cs.CR, cs.GT, cs.SI, cs.DC, cs.CY

This paper deals with security analysis of a decentralized content curation platform, which involves game-theoretic measures of performance and resilience to selfish participants. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also involves modeling and simulation of the platform, which suggests that it could belong to cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Additionally, the platform is blockchain-based, which could place it in cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.CY (Computers and Society).
